Package: ReactomeContentService4R
Title: R Interface for Reactome Content Service
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    c(person("Chi-Lam", "Poon", role = "aut", email = "clpoon807@gmail.com", 
              comment = structure("0000-0001-6298-7099", .Names = "ORCID")),
      person("Reactome", role = "cre", email = "help@reactome.org"))
Description: Reactome is a free, open-source, open access, curated and peer-reviewed knowledgebase of 
    biomolecular pathways. ReactomeContentService4R provides an interface to query data from the Reactome 
    ContentService. Pre-built functions in the package would allow users to retrieve data such as proteins, 
    pathways, along with other instances that are related to a specific gene or entity in Reactome.
